items.name: TF/TG M2F LoRA — ALPHA
items.description:
Note: Please read below for usage notes and prompting tips.

This is an experimental model that can be used to create transformation sequence images. In particular, it was trained on male-to-female (m2f) gender transformation sequences -- men getting turned into women. It's fairly good at that, but can also be used to generate similar types of transformation sequences such as breast expansion and bimbofication. It has a strong bias to starting out the image with a male figure, however, so these results will be even less consistent.

Consistency is the most difficult thing to achieve with the current version of this LoRA. Most of the results posted here are at least somewhat cherry-picked. Some sequences are easier to produce than others; likely the ones that are represented in the dataset. I would estimate that I'm happy with <25% of the outputs.

Nonetheless, I decided to post this while I work on an updated version. Enjoy!

Usage Notes:

  • Trained on base SD1.5, and it shows its best and most consistent results there, but any realistic model has a good chance of working. (I haven't gotten it working on other kinds of models.)

  • Use 0.5-0.8 strength for the LoRA; higher values have a stronger chance of inheriting some undesirable style characteristics. Lower values can still be good as well.

  • The aspect ratio of the image has a strong effect on the output. Certain image sizes will gravitate towards generating a certain number of steps. Wide aspect ratio is recommended, and an aspect ratio exceeding 2:1 works well for 5seq.

  • ControlNet is really useful for controlling the output of this LoRA. Supply an openpose input to place the desired number of figures in the output.

Prompting:

  • Add 3seq or 5seq to the prompt to guide the output towards a sequence of 3 or 5 transformation steps. It was trained on sequences ranging from 2-7, but most of those outside of 3 or 5 did not have a lot of data, so these are the strongest.

  • drawing, digital art, 3d render all seem to be the easiest styles for this LoRA to work with, but they also have a higher chance of bleeding over some styles from the training data. I've generated a lot of photo prompts as well.

  • Prompt structure that generally works well: <3seq/5seq>, <style>, <description of man>, <description of woman>, <description of scene>, e.g.

    • 3seq, (masterpiece photo), man wearing a t-shirt and shorts, woman wearing a bikini, beach

    • 5seq, (masterpiece photo), man wearing a suit, woman wearing a dress

    • 3seq, (masterpiece photo), skinny man wearing a shirt and jeans, woman with huge tits, black background

  • Generally compatible with other style or character LoRAs, though you will have to play with the strengths.

items.name: uuuuzan Style
items.description:
Version Final:

A LoRA for u_u_zan's Style based on Any_Lora.

Newest larger model has a more consistent style, but this has tradeoffs:
- Worse hands
- Touhou tends to mix into character prompts and loras
- Color pallete, or backlight effects are prominent (I personally like this)


Shouldn't need any trigger words, however adding 'u_u_zan' or 'u_u_zan style', may force the style more. Works best at weight 0.8-1.0. Clip Skip 2, however it is not required to generate good images. Trained on booru tags. Good SFW.
There were no NSFW images for training, but somehow it can do it.
Tends to apply a drawing style to background.

For best results, or results similar to mine, most anime-style models should work. Additionally, it is most recommended to use badv5/EasyNegative textual inversions.


I often use variation seed, and these do not appear in some image parameters unfortunately. I encourage you to experiment with it. I use 0.05-0.15 strength.

Should work fine with other LoRAs.

Examples done using many different models. Follow prompts to attempt replication and use given negatives for better generations.

Usage:

  • CFG Scale: 7-9

  • LoRA Weight: 0.6-0.8, 1.0

  • Should work fine for less detailed prompts. High-res fix is highly recommended

items.name: A-Zovya Photoreal
items.description:
Update June 28th, added pruned version to V2 and V2 inpainting with VAE

V2

After weeks in the making, I have a much improved model. No longer a merge, but additional training added to supplement some things I feel are missing in current models. Lots of new training for skin textures, lighting and non-asian faces to balance out the asian dominance in models. If you create a generic prompt, you'll get a greater variety of races and faces now. Skin textures are increased by a large amount, if that's not your thing, you can put detailed skin in the negative prompt and get back that airbrushed look if you like.

A photorealistic model I've been using for a little bit. I hate smooth airbrushed skin so I refined this model to be very realistic with great skin texture and details. There are 2 models, a standard and an ultra.

The Ultra model is nearly 3 times as large, but it's not 3 times as good. It is better though with a broader knowledge. You can even generate 1024x1024 in many cases. The config file is required for the Ultra model, be sure to download that too.

So I recommend using the normal version unless you have the need or vram to run the Ultra model. If you'd like to run the Ultra model with modest vram, try --medvram or --lowvram in your auto1111 startup script.

A side-by-side comparison. Link to see full-size samples with metadata. Like I said, the Ultra model isn't 3 times as good, but it is better across multiple subjects, not all. The pruned version of the Ultra model is debatable, might be better to use the normal V1 model in some cases. But all have been provided so you can make the choice yourself. For me, I use the Ultra model in every case.

Do you have requests? I've been putting in many more hours lately with this. That's my problem, not yours. But if you'd like to tip me, buy me a beer. Beer encourages me to ignore work and make AI models instead. Tip and make a request. I'll give it a shot if I can. Here at Ko-Fi

items.name: Phineas and Ferb - Candace Flynn
items.description:
If you like the LoRA, please feel free to share your generated images here and leave a review (or at least a rating) for the sake of motivation and stuff ;D

For usage guidance, look into the About this version box for more information and click on Show more to get all trigger words and combinations (The trigger words in the Details box are a pain to manage).

Please contact me here on civitAi or on Twitter if you want to provide the LoRa in a generation service.

About

Uuuuurg... This one has been tough, not only have I not been able to do any training for the last few days due to the fact that I've changed my hardware, so I've had to redo my whole setup, but hey, training is going a lot faster now (training time has practically been cut in half :D).

For quite some time now I have wanted to create a Lora of Candace from Phenias and Ferb, just for the sake of nostalgia. ^^

But to be hornets: Her character design is hell for AI training. The way her hair and head is shaped is just not human, but well, if you look at her brother, there is probably something genetically wrong in that family regarding the head shape, because pretty much everyone else in that series has a proper face/hair shape.

Training

I watched half of the first session and had enough material to train on. I know that she sometimes wears different clothes, but only for half an episode or so, so there is not much data to get, so I mainly trained her on her red shirt/white skirt combo with 43 shots total.

candace_flynn <lora:CandaceFlynn_v1:1>

I recommend playing around with different checkpoints because her hair will most likely be interpreted differently depending on the checkpoint used, some ignore the shape, some create a ponytail or ahoge from her hairstyle, you can try adding these hairstyles to the negative prompt for less weird results.

items.name: Penelope Cruz
items.description:
Penélope Cruz is a Spanish actress, winner of an Academy Award for Best Actress in a Supporting Role in 2008.

Even though SD recognizes Penélope quite well without the need for a specific embedding, I've always thought the resemblance was quite improvable (as is the case with many celebrities), and that's what moved me to create this TI, which I hope you'll find an upgrade compared to the "default" SD version.

It's a 1000-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (p3cruz:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, sexy pirate outfit, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6, bandana, holding a gun".

items.name: Something
items.description:
all rights and congratulations to: NoCrypt https://huggingface.co/NoCrypt/SomethingV2_2

SomethingV2.2

Welcome to SomethingV2.2 - an improved anime latent diffusion model from SomethingV2

A lot of things are being discovered lately, such as a way to merge model using mbw automatically, offset noise to get much darker result, and even VAE tuning. This model is intended to use all of those features as the improvements, here's some improvements that have been made:

Can't trust the numbers? Here's some proof

Recommended settings

  • VAE: None (Baked in model, blessed2)

  • Clip Skip: 2

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

  • CFG Scale: 7 ± 5

  • Recommended Positive Prompt: masterpiece, best quality, negative space, (bioluminescence:1.2), darkness, dark background

  • Recommended Negative Prompt: EasyNegative

  • For better results, using hires fix is a must.

  • Hires upscaler: Latent (any variant, such as nearest-exact)

Recipe

Due to SD-Silicon's Terms of use. I must specify how the model was made

Model AModel BInterpolation MethodWeightNamedpepmkmpsilicon29-darkMBWReverse CosinedpepsilisomethingV2_1dpepsiliMBWCosineSomethingV2_2 rawSomethingV2_2 rawBlessed2 VAEBake VAE-SomethingV2_2

Why not call it SomethingV4?

Since this model was based on SomethingV2 and there's not THAT much of improvements in some condition. Calling it V4 is just not right at the moment 😅

items.name: Persis Khambatta -- Indian Actress/Model (Star Trek TMP "Lt. Ilia")
items.description:
Actress/Model Persis Khambatta

This is a textual inversion of actress/model Persis Khambatta, best known for her role as the bald-headed Deltan navigator in Star Trek: The Motion Picture. She was born in Bombay, India, and was Miss India in 1965. She also had roles in movies such as Nighthawks and The Wilby Conspiracy (with Michael Caine and Sydney Poitier). She is also distinguished as the first Indian female performer to present an award at the Oscars.

I have to say I have a LOT of satisfaction finally posting this TI. I've always thought Persis was a hauntingly beautiful and sexy woman -- sadly, she passed away fairly early in life in the late 1990s. Her beauty remains with us however in a form such as this.

I'm especially glad that this TI came out to my satisfaction (and hopefully yours) as the source material for her imagery is often low resolution or in black and white. I sourced imagery from screencaps of The Wilby Conspiracy (where she has a suspenseful scene as a sexy dental assistant with Sydney Poitier), as this is where I thought she looked absolutely alluring. After a number of tries ending up with monstrosities, I finally was able to get the right settings and training to get some lovely generation going.

Let me know how you like this TI. I might give yet another go at a V2 later, or learn to do LoRAs and then try that.

items.name: Andrei Tarkovsky Style
items.description:
Andrei Tarkovsky was a Soviet film director, widely regarded as one of the greatest filmmakers in the history of cinema. His films are known for their poetic and philosophical nature, exploring existential themes, memory, spirituality, and the human condition.

Tarkovsky's filmmaking style is characterized by long takes, slow pacing, and a deliberate attention to visual composition. He often used surreal and symbolic imagery, creating a sense of timelessness and inviting viewers to reflect on deeper meanings within his films.

One of Tarkovsky's most renowned works is "Solaris" (1972), a science fiction film that explores the complexities of human relationships and the nature of consciousness. The film, like many of Tarkovsky's works, delves into philosophical questions and psychological depths, challenging viewers to contemplate the mysteries of existence.

Tarkovsky's films often feature atmospheric and visually striking cinematography, with shots carefully crafted to create a sense of atmosphere and evoke emotions. His use of natural settings and poetic imagery adds to the contemplative and meditative quality of his works.

While his films were sometimes met with challenges and censorship by Soviet authorities, Tarkovsky remained committed to his artistic vision and produced a body of work that has had a lasting impact on world cinema.

Andrei Tarkovsky's films are considered profound and influential, admired for their depth, thoughtfulness, and poetic sensibility. His unique approach to storytelling and visual language continues to inspire filmmakers and audiences alike, making him a highly revered figure in the world of cinema.

items.name: ⭐️EZ LoRa Downloader - WebUI Extension⭐️
items.description:
Introducing EZ Lora Downloader.

What is the most inconvenient thing while using WebUI? 

When creating images by referencing other people's work, it's not easy to download the Lora file that the person used without knowing downloadable or not.


With EZ Lora Downloader, you can solve this problem at once.

Here's how it works:

  1. Select the image you want to replicate 

  2. Send to T2I or Send to I2I(Copying generation data is also an option.)

  3. Click "Search LoRa".

  4. EZ Lora Downloader will display the downloadable Lora files that you don't have.

  5. Download the one you need.

  6. Refresh and Generate!

You can browse various pictures that you might want to reproduce on the Feed tab.

  1. Newest : Real-time images by WebUI users

  2. Popular : Most popular pictures

  3. Favorite : Pictures that you have liked (with a recommendation feature to be added in the future).

  4. Customize your feed! Change your nickname and promote yourself.

  • In the future, we plan to improve the extension so that you can download missing items such as Models, Samplers, and other extensions.

Feel free to contact me on Discord!
https://discord.gg/wyK3Ftu3

Installation

If downloading directly:

  1. Create a folder named "sd_feed" in the "extensions" folder within the WebUI, and extract the compressed file there.

If installing from within the WebUI:

  1. Click the "install from url" button in the "extensions" tab.

  2. Enter https://github.com/todhm/sd_feed.

  3. Click the "install" button.

If cloning from Git:

  1. In the terminal, navigate to the "extensions" folder and enter the command "git clone https://github.com/todhm/sd_feed.git".
